<page sig="aaa1r">
<section type="Title-page">
<heading>
AN 
ALPHABETICAL DICTIONARY, 
Wherein all 
ENGLISH WORDS
According to their 

VARIOUS SIGNIFICATIONS, 
Are either referred to their Places in the 
PHILOSOPHICAL TABLES, 
Or explained by such Words as are in those 
TABLES.
</heading>

LONDON, 

Printed by <f type="i">J. M.<f type="r"> for <f type="i">Samuel Gellibrand<f type="r"> and 
<f type="i">Iohn Martin<f type="r">, 1668.
</section>
</page>

</page>

<section type="a" object="An Advertisement to the Reader">
<heading>
AN 
ADVERTISEMENT 
TO THE 
READER.
<heading>

FOr the better understanding of the References in the following 
Dictionary, the Reader is desired to take notice, that the Ab&shy;
breviations therein used, are thus to be explained;

The Literal Figures, as I, II, V, <f type="i">&amp;c.</f> denote
the order of the Differences
under each Genus; and the other Figures, the order of the
<emend err="the"></emend>Species under each Difference. So the word <f type="i">Sheep</f> in
the Dictio&shy;
nary is marked Be. II.2. The meaning of which is, That the thing
signified by that word is described in the Philosophical Tables under 
the Genus of BEAST, the second difference, and the second Species. 
And <f type="i">Goat</f> is Be. II.2. <expan type="A."><term lang="la">Affinis.</term></expan> (<f type="i">i.e.</f>) 'tis joyned as an Affinis to the same 
Species.

The Design of the Philosophical Tables is to enumerate and describe 
all kinds of <f type="i">Things</f> and <f type="i">Notions</f>: And the Design of this Dictionary, 
is to reckon up and explain all kinds of <f type="i">words</f>, or <f type="i">names</f> of things.

And that the Reader may the better understand the usefulness of 
having all words set down according to their different Acceptions, 
and by what kind of Analogy they come to be used in such various 
sences (which is one of the particular advantages of this Dictionary) 
I shall here select out of it one particular Instance, for each of these 
several kinds of words, <f type="i">viz.</f> a <f type="i">Substantive</f>, an <f type="i">Adjective</f>, a <f type="i">Verb</f>, a
<f type="i">Par&shy;
ticle</f>; by which it will be easie to understand any of the rest.

So the word <f type="i">CORRVPTION</f>, according to that Notion of it which 
is

<f type="i">Primary</f> and proper, doth denote the<f type="i">Being</f>, or <f type="i">Making</f> of a <f type="i">thing,
evil</f>, or <f type="i">worse</f>, whether by
<f type="i">Admixtion</f> with that which is bad, and then it is of the same 
importance with the word <f type="i">Defiling</f>.
<f type="i">Privation</f>, as to a thing
<f type="i">Being</f>, so corruption is <f type="i">destroying</f>.
<f type="i">Vsefulness</f>, so corruption is <f type="i">spoiling</f>.
<f type="i">Secondary</f>, as applied to things
<f type="i">Natural</f>, so Corruption will denote according to the Degree 
of it, either <f type="i">Infection</f>, or <f type="i">Decay</f>, or <f type="i">Putrefaction</f>.
<f type="i">Moral</f>, whether more
<f type="i">General</f>, so it denotes the Evilness of the mind or manners, 
<f type="i">Vnholiness, Viciousness</f>.
<f type="i">Special</f>, so 'tis peculiarly applied to <f type="i">Vnchastity</f> and <f type="i">Bribery</f>.
</page>

<page sig="aaa3r">
So the word <f type="i">CLEAR</f>, may signifie either
<f type="i">Entire of it self</f>; so clearly is <f type="i">wholly</f>.
<f type="i">Not mingled with others</f>; so Clear is <f type="i">Simple</f>. 
specially not with worse; so Clear is <f type="i">Pure</f>.
<f type="i">Being free from impediments</f>, or not being hindered from
<f type="i">Being, doing</f>, or <f type="i">receiving</f>, which notion of Clear may 
be often exprest by the Transcendental mark of Perfe&shy;
ctive. There may be Instances of it given in every Ge&shy;
nus; as particularly,
<f type="i">Quality</f>, whether
<f type="i">Natural Power</f>, so a clear sight or understanding is 
a good s. or u. It is applied to the
<f type="i">Mind</f>, as a <f type="i">clear Wit</f>, or <f type="i">Spirit</f>.
<f type="i">Body</f>, so we say one is clear of sickness or pain, has 
a clear skin, <f type="i">&amp;c.</f>
<f type="i">Habit</f>, as a <f type="i">clear Reputation</f>, that is a good R. 
sp. Sagacity and Sincerity are thus called Clear&shy;
ness.
<f type="i">Manners</f>, as <f type="i">Clear Dealing</f>, that is Candor or Frank&shy;
ness.
<f type="i">Sensible Quality.</f>
Visible, as <f type="i">clear weather</f>, or sky or water, <f type="i">&amp;c.</f>
Audible, as <f type="i">clear sound</f>.
<f type="i">Sickness</f>, as <f type="i">clear of any disease</f> (i. e.) not Infected, 
or not Diseased.
<f type="i">Relation.</f>
<f type="i">Civil</f>, as a <f type="i">Clear Estate</f>.
<f type="i">Judicial</f>, as <f type="i">Clear of any Crime</f>.
<f type="i">Military</f>, as <f type="i">Clear Coast</f>.
<f type="i">Ecclesiastic</f>, as <f type="i">Clear of any Censure</f>.
<f type="i">Being Done</f>, so Clear is <f type="i">Easie</f>, or not difficult; <f type="i">Being Known</f>, 
so Clear is <f type="i">Plain</f> or manifest; <f type="i">Being come to</f>, or <f type="i">Passed 
through</f>, so Clear is <f type="i">Accessible</f>, or <f type="i">Passable</f>, or <f type="i">Empty</f>.

So the word <f type="i">DELIVER</f>, according to its primary sence, is the mo&shy;
tion (Met.) or the passing of a thing, or of the Possession of it, or of
the Power over it, from one to another. It is commonly used in rela&shy;
tion either to the 
<f type="i">Subject</f>, or thing deliver'd, whether
<f type="i">Things</f>; so Deliver may signifie <f type="i">Depositing, Paying, Resigning</f>.
<f type="i">Words</f>, as to the
<f type="i">Matter</f>, whether concerning
<f type="i">Fact</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Narration</f>
<f type="i">Doctrine</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Teaching</f>
<f type="i">Manner</f>, whether
<f type="i">Immediately</f> by
<f type="i">Mouth</f>, so to deliver, is to <f type="i">speak</f>.
<f type="i">Pen</f>, so to deliver, is to <f type="i">write</f>
<f type="i">Mediately</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Tradition</f>
<f type="i">Terms</f> of this motion, either <f type="i">from</f> a
</page>

<page sig="aaa3v">
<f type="i">Better</f> condition <f type="i">to</f> a <f type="i">worse</f>, being used
<f type="i">Passively</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Dereliction</f>
<f type="i">Actively</f>, whether
<f type="i">Involuntary</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">yielding</f>
<f type="i">Voluntary</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Betraying</f>
<f type="i">Worse</f> condition <f type="i">to</f> a <f type="i">better</f>.
<f type="i">Temporal</f>, whether by way of
<f type="i">Prevention</f>, so Delivering is <f type="i">Preserving</f>, or <f type="i">Causing to escape:</f>
<f type="i">Remedy</f>, from 
<f type="i">Captivity</f>, so to deliver, is to <f type="i">Vncaptivate</f>.
<f type="i">Bondage</f>, so to deliver, is to <f type="i">Vnslave</f>.
<f type="i">Prison</f>, so to deliver, is to <f type="i">Vnimprison</f>.
<f type="i">Danger of Child-birth</f>, so to deliver, is the 
Active of <f type="i">Parturition</f>.
<f type="i">Eternal</f>, so delivering is <f type="i">Redemption</f>.

So the Particle BY, is sometimes used in the sence of an
<f type="i">Integral</f>, signifying the notion of <f type="i">Digression</f> or <f type="i">Accessory</f>, as <f type="i">on 
the by</f>; and is of the same importance with such kind of Ne&shy;
gatives, as not <f type="i">principal</f>, not <f type="i">pertinent</f>, not <f type="i">public</f>, not <f type="i">ordi&shy;
nary</f>; as a <f type="i">By-way</f>: And sometimes 'tis used to denote a
common speech implying something of contempt, as a <f type="i">By-&shy;
word</f>.
<f type="i">Preposition</f>
<f type="i">Causal,</f> 
Efficient, <f type="i">By such an Author</f>.
Instrumental, <f type="i">Slain by the sword</f>.
Final, or end, <f type="i">By reason of, &amp;c.</f>
Local or Temporal, being sometimes used in that same
sence with those other Prepositions.
<f type="i">Before</f>, as, By God, (<f type="i">i.</f>) before God.
<f type="i">At</f>, as, Come by, (<f type="i">i.</f>) obtain, or come at.
<f type="i">In</f>, as, by day, (<f type="i">i.</f>) in the day time.
<f type="i">Through</f>, as, by such a street,(<f type="i">i.</f>) through such a street.
<f type="i">Besides</f>, as, by the mark, (<f type="i">i.</f>) besides.
<f type="i">Adverbs</f> denoting the Circumstance of Nearness, whether
<f type="i">Local.</f> So By, or hard by, is near such a <f type="i">Place</f>.
<f type="i">Temporal.</f> So By and by, is nearness in <f type="i">Time</f>, signifying 
future (dim.)
</page>

<page sig="aaa4r">
Besides those Phraseologies wherein the Particle is used to signifie 
the <f type="i">Manner</f> of things, as, <f type="i">By the By, By the Great, By Retail, By it 
self</f>, &amp;c. Which Phrases are to be expressed by the Adverbs Neuter 
of <f type="i">Digression, Aggregate, Segregate, Solitary</f>, &amp;c. So those Forms of 
Speech, <f type="i">By course, By the day</f>, or <f type="i">day by day, By degrees, By turns, 
House by House, Year by Year</f>, &amp;c. are to be expressed by the Adverbs 
of <f type="i">Course, Day, Degree, Turn, House, Year</f>, with the Transcendental 
Note of Segregate.
</section>
</page>

<page sig="aaa4v">
</page>

<section type="Dictionary">
<heading>
The Alphabetical DICTIONARY.
</heading>
